  "summary": "The graph contains 9 group nodes and 18 directed edges with relatively high density (~0.25) and forms a single connected component (no isolated groups). Nodes represent layered modules (Routes, Controllers, Services, Models, Utils, Config, Types, Middlewares, Tests) with Services and Utils acting as primary hubs (highest in/out degree). All edges are import relationships (directed), showing a clear layered chain routes→controllers→services→models and many cross-cutting imports into utils and config; tests and middlewares also import config/models. Notable patterns include self-imports in Services and Utils and circular coupling (Services↔Config and a larger cycle Services→Utils→Config→Routes→Controllers→Services), indicating potential tight coupling despite an otherwise layered API surface."
